For the justice administered by God is one thing, that by men, another, as we shall shew hercafter. Nor again can we argue that, because (16- scendants receive honours and rewards for the merit of their ancestors, therefore it is just that they should be punished for their crimes. For benefits are of such nature, by their matter, that they may be beo stowed upon any without injury, but punishments are not.
